#Symptoms - Eczema - EA8Z
The patient with atopic dermatitis reacts easily to irritants, food, and environmental allergens and becomes very itchy, leading to: Redness. Skin edema (swelling). Itching and dryness. Crusting or cracking. Flaking. Blistering. Oozing or bleeding. It is sometimes also called as "the itch that rashes" because the itchiness precedes the rash or scratching the itchy skin may cause the rash.